<item>
            <title>[HBASE-9641] We should have a way to provide table level based ACL.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9641</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Today we can grant rights to users based on the user / table / column family / family. When there is thousands of users and you want to add a new table, it&apos;s long to add back everyone to the table.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should be able to provide a table based ACL. Something like &quot;grant_table &amp;lt;table_name&amp;gt; &amp;lt;rights&amp;gt; [ &amp;lt;column familiy&amp;gt; [ &amp;lt;column&amp;gt; ]]&quot; to give specific rights to a table for ALL the users.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
