                            <comment id="13775707" author="mbertozzi" created="Mon, 23 Sep 2013 22:06:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AccessControlList already talk about groups, even if they are not really implemented.&lt;br/&gt;
maybe that is a more generic way to do that?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13777220" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 07:18:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It sounds like what you are asking for is role based access control, where you define a few roles, do grants to tables as appropriate, and then manage perms for individual users through role membership. We envisioned groups (especially as Hadoop group lookup is pluggable) as a way to achieve that without full-on RBAC as Matteo suggests. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13777642" author="jmspaggi" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 15:49:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Groups will definitively be a good option to achieve that. Even if it&apos;s not exactly the same thing. Worst case, just need to have one group per table, and so we can define rights per tables working with the related group...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So if I understand correctly, this as been started, but is not fully developed? Do we already have another JIRA to follow that?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
